trend_summary: Between the earliest and latest scenes, cropland mosaics contract while forest cover steadily expands, signalling farmland abandonment. Low-density dwellings spread a little along the north-east highway and some new farm buildings emerge, yet no continuous urban fabric forms. Overall the landscape remains dominantly rural, with only marginal growth of dispersed housing.
notable_changes: Progressive regrowth of woodland into several former crop fields, especially in the western half
Minor extension of residential cul-de-sacs and driveways near the main north-east road
Appearance of new agricultural sheds/barns on two farmsteads in the south-east quadrant
Realignment and slight widening of the arterial road on the north-east edge
